            <signavio:signavioLabel align="left" distance="7.499949" from="0" orientation="ll" ref="text_name" to="1" valign="bottom" x="1714.5000509066638" y="616.7037081958633"/>
         </extensionElements>
      </sequenceFlow>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-2247E1B4-C9DE-4352-8079-3EE941B28021" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>L3 Description-
Continue to receive deliveries from supplier and informally relay findings to necessary individuals. This is intended to keep all parties involved informed of any signs of potential deviation from plans.​</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-1FD71EEB-15F5-46D0-BC7D-0D4A3A61F1FC" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Reporting:​

Supplier Performance Operational Details/KPIs  (driven by individual L3 processes across functions).   Ex:   Contract process KPIs, delivery performance, PO commit/decommit, Quality process controls/audits/remediation    
 *  Includes both standard S4 report to call operational supplier data  and  ECA based dashboards​


Supplier Management Overview (summary level) ​

Analytics/Reporting based on ECA data.  No direct S4 connection.​

Segmentation drives the level of performance and actions to manage supplier​

               -  Supplier Hierarchy summary - global/children, associated contract(s), spends/commits, segmentation level, contacts, contract owner​

               -  Contract Overview - contractID, contract name, amendments, owners, committs/paid against, expiry​

               -  Spends breakdown by TCOO / sourcing category;  high level sourcing org​

               -  Responsibility &amp; Risk:  deliverables assigned, criteria, and status​

               -  Supplier report card:  line items, owners, due dates, status, comments, quality​

               -  Supplier improvement plans (includes Quality):  SOR is TBD​</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-BC2A3718-2E6C-45BE-9CD0-BB36512E79DF" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Boundary Apps:​

Performance management  online SRC, theGrid, Supplier 360 (SDM, SAM),  3rd parties (SRS, Security Scorecard)​

Social responsibility deliverables (Bapp: Graphite, suppliersoft, email)​

Supplier training (Bapp: docebo)​</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-170 Monitor Supplier Performance</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-5105BB70-8781-49DF-871D-FF7ADC6083DA" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
